  "text": "Setting 4: Heterogeneous gene effects. Previous studies have shown that GSEA is less likely to detect sets of genes containing both positive and negative associations with the phenotype. [CITATION_1] This is because, by pooling together correlations, GSEA assumes that the genes in a set have a coordinated effect -that is, that they all act in the same direction. In this simulation, we examine this aspect of GSEA further and demonstrate that the exhibition of heterogeneous effects among genes in a set deteriorates the statistical power of GSEA.",
